    <h1>Classic Beet Borscht</h1>

    <p>
      Borscht is the perfect cold-weather soup — it is rich, earthy, and has just the right amount of sour. I love borscht's deep ruby-red color, rib-sticking heartiness, and the fact that it is full of vegetables, which feels like a win come wintertime.
      Borscht is endlessly riffable. Plus, it is a great way to use up the vegetables you have on hand. Because the beets and red cabbage will stain any other vegetables you add a bright red, they will end up blending in seamlessly (just watch out for your shirt and kitchen towels!). So if your memories of borscht consist of the sickly sweet jarred variety, you owe it to yourself to give the homemade variety a chance.
    </p>

