      <li>1 pound boneless beef chuck roast or stew meat</li>
      <li>2 teaspoons kosher salt, divided, plus more as needed</li>
      <li>2 tablespoons olive oil, divided</li>
      <li>1 (6-ounce) can tomato paste</li>
      <li>2 (32-ounce) cartons low-sodium vegetable or chicken broth (about 8 cups)</li>
      <li>2 dried bay leaves</li>
      <li>1 1/4 pounds loose red beets (about 3 large)</li>
      <li>3 medium carrots (about 10 ounces)</li>
      <li>1 large russet potato (about 8 ounces)</li>
      <li>1/2 small red cabbage (about 1 pound)</li>
      <li>1/4 cup red wine vinegar</li>
      <li>1/4 cup packed light brown sugar</li>
    </ul>

